## Codebase Patterns

- Build uses esbuild for JS output and `tsc --emitDeclarationOnly` for `.d.ts` files.
- `tsconfig.build.json` extends `tsconfig.json` and excludes `example/` and `test/`; it also sets `rootDir: ./src` so declarations land at `dist/index.d.ts` (not `dist/src/index.d.ts`).
- `tsconfig.json` must include `"ignoreDeprecations": "6.0"` for TypeScript 6.x compatibility (`esModuleInterop: false` is deprecated).
- `.eslintignore` excludes generated `.js` files in `bin/` (same reason `dist/*` and `test/*.js` are excluded).
- Three entrypoints: `src/index.ts`, `src/render.ts`, `src/context.ts` — each produces ESM, CJS, and `.d.ts` outputs.
- Test harness: `esbuild --bundle ./test/index.ts | tapout` — pipes bundled test JS through tapout (Playwright-based browser runner). The `--bundle` flag is required so esbuild resolves all imports before piping to tapout.
- `listFiles: true` in `tsconfig.json` causes tsc to print included file paths to stdout — this is normal noise, not errors.

