## 2026-06-27 - US-005
- Created `src/builders.ts` with:
  - `propDSL` object: `number()`, `string()`, `boolean()`, `json<T>()`, `schema()`, `prop()` methods
  - `ComponentBuilder<Props>` class with `withProps()` and `setup()` fluent methods
  - `define(tagName)` function (entry point, will be exported from index in US-008)
  - Internal helpers: `isPropOnly()`, `isStandardSchema()`, `normalizePropDef()`
- Updated `src/types.ts`: added `PropertyOnlyProp<T>` interface; added it to `PropDef<T>` union; updated `PropType<D>` conditional to handle `PropertyOnlyProp<T>`
- Updated `src/factory.ts`: changed `FactoryConfig<Props>` constraint from `Record<string, PropDef>` to `FactoryProps` (= `Record<string, Coercer<unknown>>`), and typed `props: Props` (was `props: FactoryProps`). This allows TypeScript to infer the coercer types from the `props` object and provide correct signal types in `setup()` callbacks. Removed now-unused `PropDef` import.
- Added 7 US-005 tests to `test/index.ts` covering all prop variants and attribute observability.
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - `FactoryConfig<Props extends FactoryProps>` with `props: Props` (not `props: FactoryProps`) lets TypeScript infer `Props` from the coercer record, so `ctx.props.count()` gets the concrete return type (number) instead of `unknown`.
  - Changing `factory`'s generic constraint from `Props extends Record<string, PropDef>` to `Props extends FactoryProps` narrows what can be passed but is fine: the builders always convert PropDef to coercers first. `Coercer<T>` satisfies `PropDef<T>` anyway.
  - `propDSL.json<T>()` uses `coerceJson as Coercer<T | undefined>` — the `<T>` is provided by the caller at use site, not inferred.
  - Property-only props (`p.prop(initial)`) are kept out of `observedAttrNames`; the factory's `connectedCallback` only updates the signal when `getAttribute` returns non-null, so property-only props safely preserve their value across reconnects.
  - For `ComponentBuilder.setup()`, cast the user callback as `any` before passing to `factory` to avoid the type mismatch between builder's `Props extends Record<string, PropDef>` and factory's narrower `Props extends FactoryProps`.
  - `type PS = PropsSignals<Props>` accidentally used as the `Refs` type arg in `SetupContext<Props, PS, any>` causes TS2344; always use `any` for unused type parameters in SetupContext inside builders.
