## 2026-06-27 - US-009
- Implemented `src/context.ts` with `createContext<T>()`, `provide(element, token, value)`, `resolveContextSignal(element, token)`, and `onContextAvailable(id, callback)`.
- Context values are stored as alien-signals signals in a `WeakMap<Element, Map<symbol, Signal<unknown>>>`. When `provide()` is called again with a new value, the existing signal is updated in place, so any subscribed effects re-run automatically.
- Pending consumers are tracked in `Map<symbol, Set<() => void>>`. When `provide()` is called, `notifyPending` fires all registered callbacks for that context id.
- Updated `src/factory.ts` `connectedCallback` to:
  - Build a reactive `Proxy` for `contexts`: reading a key inside a `ctx.effect` calls the provider's signal, creating a subscription so effects react to context changes.
  - Defer setup via `tryRunSetup` / `tryRunSetupIfConnected` until all `.withContexts()` declared tokens are resolved in the ancestor DOM.
  - Register `onContextAvailable` listeners (pushed to both a local `cancelCallbacks` array and `cleanups`) so setup runs when the last required context becomes available. Both arrays are safe to clean up multiple times.
  - Move `collectRefs` into `tryRunSetup` so refs are only queried when setup actually runs.
- Updated `src/setup-context.ts`: `ctx.consume(token)` now walks up the DOM via `resolveContextSignal` and returns the current signal value (or `undefined` if no provider).
- Updated `test/index.ts`: updated the US-006 `withContexts` test and `withProps+withRefs+withContexts chain` test to wrap elements in a provider div and call `provide()` before connecting to the DOM (required because deferred setup is now real). Added 5 US-009 tests.
- All 70 tests pass; lint clean; typecheck clean.
- Files changed: `src/context.ts`, `src/factory.ts`, `src/setup-context.ts`, `test/index.ts`, `specs/prd.json`, `progress.log`
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - The `isConnected` guard for deferred setup must only apply to callbacks registered via `onContextAvailable` (the async path). The synchronous `tryRunSetup` path (called directly from `connectedCallback`) must NOT have the guard, or tests calling `connectedCallback()` directly on disconnected elements will silently skip setup.
  - Context signals are stored by `token.id` (symbol), not by token reference, so manually created tokens (`{ id: Symbol('x') }`) and `createContext()`-created tokens are interchangeable as long as the id matches.
  - Any test that uses `.withContexts()` must now provide those contexts before or immediately after connecting the element; setup is deferred until all declared contexts resolve.
  - `resolveContextSignal` walks `element.parentElement` (not `element` itself), so `provide()` must be called on an ancestor, not on the element itself.
